## Memory System — Recording Rules

Every significant session must produce records in:

| File | When |
|------|------|
| `memory/MODIFICATION_LOG.md` | After every significant change |
| `memory/plans/PLAN-XXXX.md` | Before executing complex or structural changes |
| `memory/decisions/DECISION-XXX.md` | When an architectural decision is made |
| `memory/logs/DEBUG-HISTORY.md` | After every resolved bug (format: ERR-0001, ERR-0002...) |
| `memory/progress.md` | When a module changes state |

---

## Session Closure

Before ending any session:
1. Run `memory/logs/SESSION-AUDIT-CHECKLIST.md`
2. Update `memory/MODIFICATION_LOG.md` with done/changed/pending
3. Session must reach **PASS** — do not close on FAIL

